✅ 3. GPS SETTINGS MOVED TO ADMIN PANEL
   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   
   ✓ Previous: GPS settings in employee login expander
   ✓ Now:     GPS controls in Admin → Settings tab (admin_settings() function)
   
   Old Location:
   └─ render_login() → with st.expander("📍 GPS Location")
   
   New Location:
   └─ render_admin_panel() → tab5: "⚙️ SETTINGS" → admin_settings()
   
   Removed from Employee Flow:
   ├─ ❌ GPS location input on login screen
   ├─ ❌ "Confirm Location" button for employees
   ├─ ❌ Employee ability to fake GPS location
   └─ ❌ Every login requires GPS setup
   
   Added to Admin Panel:
   ├─ ✓ Three inputs: Latitude, Longitude, Radius (km)
   ├─ ✓ "Save GPS Settings" button (admin only)
   ├─ ✓ Settings change log showing who changed what
   ├─ ✓ Previous settings visible in history
   ├─ ✓ Timestamp for all changes
   └─ ✓ Confirmation message on save
   
   New Database Table:
   └─ gps_settings:
      ├─ id          → Record ID
      ├─ latitude    → Office latitude
      ├─ longitude   → Office longitude
      ├─ radius_km   → Geofence radius
      ├─ updated_by  → Which admin changed it
      └─ updated_at  → When it was changed
   
   New Functions:
   ├─ db_get_gps_settings()    → Retrieves current GPS settings
   ├─ db_update_gps_settings() → Saves new settings + logs
   ├─ admin_settings()         → Admin UI for GPS control
   └─ db_log_admin_action()    → Logs admin actions
   
   How It Works:
   1. Employee logs in without setting GPS
   2. Employee can still enter GPS in login expander (for own location check)
   3. Admin goes to Settings tab
   4. Admin updates office location (only if authorized)
   5. Change logged to admin_logs table
   6. All future logins use new GPS settings


✅ 4. ADMIN PERMISSION-BASED GPS CONTROL
   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   
   ✓ Previous: Anyone with admin password could do anything
   ✓ Now:     Role-based permissions system
   
   Permission System:
   
   ADMIN_PERMISSIONS Dictionary:
   ────────────────────────────────
   ADMIN_PERMISSIONS = {
       "admin": {
           "gps_control": True,      # Can modify GPS
           "device_reset": True,     # Can reset devices
           "alerts": True            # Can manage alerts
       },
       # Add more admins here...
   }
   
   Permission Types:
   ├─ gps_control    → Can modify office location/geofence
   ├─ device_reset   → Can reset employee devices
   ├─ alerts         → Can manage security alerts
   └─ (Extensible)   → Add more permissions as needed
   
   Admin Login Flow:
   ────────────────────
   1. Render admin login (render_admin_login)
   2. Request admin ID (username)
   3. Request admin password
   4. Check: pwd == ADMIN_PASS AND admin_id in ADMIN_PERMISSIONS
   5. If valid: st.session_state.admin_logged_in = True
   6. If invalid: Show error "Invalid credentials"
   
   GPS Control Permission Check:
   ────────────────────────────────
   In admin_settings():
   
   admin_perms = ADMIN_PERMISSIONS.get(st.session_state.admin_name, {})
   if not admin_perms.get("gps_control"):
       st.error("❌ You don't have GPS control permission")
       return
   
   Non-Authorized Admin Behavior:
   ├─ ❌ Cannot see Settings tab
   ├─ ❌ Gets error: "You don't have GPS control permission"
   ├─ ❌ Cannot save GPS changes
   ├─ ⚠️  Admin action logged in audit trail
   └─ ✓ Other tabs (Alerts, Reports, Devices) still accessible (if permitted)
   
   Authorized Admin Behavior:
   ├─ ✓ Can see Settings tab
   ├─ ✓ Can modify Latitude/Longitude
   ├─ ✓ Can adjust Radius (km)
   ├─ ✓ Changes saved to gps_settings table
   ├─ ✓ Action logged with admin name & timestamp
   ├─ ✓ Can view change history
   └─ ✓ Success notification shown
   
   How to Add/Modify Admins:
   ────────────────────────────
   Edit ADMIN_PERMISSIONS in code:
   
   ADMIN_PERMISSIONS = {
       "admin": {
           "gps_control": True,
           "device_reset": True,
           "alerts": True
       },
       "manager1": {
           "gps_control": False,     # Manager can't change GPS
           "device_reset": True,
           "alerts": True
       },
       "super_admin": {
           "gps_control": True,
           "device_reset": True,
           "alerts": True
       }
   }
   
   Updated Password:
   ├─ Load from .env: ADMIN_PASS=your_password
   ├─ All admins use same password (or update code for per-user)
   └─ Each admin has different username


